  "label": "Vespera Tertius Cinderwood",
  "description": "Vespera Tertius Cinderwood forms a low, ash-laden forest rooted in fissured basalt, where blackened trunks rise in dense, wind-scoured ranks. A constant electrostatic charge clings to bark and drifting cinders, and violet lightning along the horizon throws stark, intermittent relief across the canopy. The ground remains carpeted in powder-fine soot over glassy impact slag, swallowing footfalls and preserving little but shallow, wind-cut impressions. Bruise-colored auroral glare stains the upper boughs and sustains a perpetual twilight beneath the rift-shadowed sky.",
